    h2 Stepper App Methods
    p Let's look at related App methods to work with Stepper:
    .method-wrap
      p
        span.method app.stepper.create(<span>parameters</span>)
        | - create Stepper instance
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter parameters
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">object</span>. Object with stepper parameters
      p.method-returns Method returns created Stepper's instance

    .method-wrap
      p
        span.method app.stepper.destroy(<span>el</span>)
        | - destroy Stepper instance
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter el
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector) or <span class="parameter-type">object</span>. Stepper element or Stepper instance to destroy.
    .method-wrap
      p
        span.method app.stepper.get(<span>el</span>)
        | - get Stepper instance by HTML element
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter el
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector). Stepper element.
      p.method-returns Method returns Stepper's instance
    .method-wrap
      p
        span.method app.stepper.getValue(<span>el</span>)
        | - get Stepper value
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter el
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector). Stepper element.
      p.method-returns Method returns stepper value
    .method-wrap
      p
        span.method app.stepper.setValue(<span>el</span>, <span>value</span>)
        | - set new Stepper value
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter el
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector). Stepper element.
        li
          span.parameter value
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">number</span>
      p.method-returns Method returns Stepper's instance
    h2 Stepper Parameters
    p Now let's look at list of available parameters we need to create Stepper:
    table.params-table
      thead
        tr
          th Parameter
          th Type
          th Default
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          td el
          td HTMLElement<br>string
          td
          td Stepper element. HTMLElement or string with CSS selector of stepper element
        tr
          td inputEl
          td HTMLElement<br>string
          td
          td Stepper input element or CSS selector of input element. If not specified, will try to look for `<input>` inside of stepper element
        tr
          td step
          td number
          td 1
          td Minimal step between values
        tr
          td min
          td number
          td 0
          td Minimum value
        tr
          td max
          td number
          td 100
          td Maximum value
        tr
          td value
          td number
          td 0
          td Initial value
        tr
          td wraps
          td boolean
          td false
          td When enabled, incrementing beyond maximum value sets value to minimum value; likewise, decrementing below minimum value sets value to maximum value
        tr
          td autorepeat
          td boolean
          td false
          td When enabled it will repeatedly increase/decrease values while you tap and hold plus/minus buttons
        tr
          td autorepeatDynamic
          td boolean
          td false
          td When enabled it will increase autorepeat ratio based on how long you hold the button
        tr
          td valueEl
          td HTMLElement<br>string
          td
          td Stepper value element or CSS selector of this element where Stepper will insert value. If not specified, and there is no `inputEl` passed will try to look for `<div class="stepper-value">` inside of stepper element
        tr
          td formatValue
          td function (value)
          td
          td Function to format value in required format. It accepts current value and must return new formatted value;
        tr
          td manualInputMode
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables manual input mode. This mode allows to type value from keyboard and check fractional part with defined accurancy. Also, `step` parameter is ignored when typing in this mode.
        tr
          td decimalPoint
          td number
          td 4
          td Number of digits after dot, when in manual input mode.
        tr
          td buttonsEndInputMode
          td boolean
          td true
          td Disables manual input mode on Stepper's minus or plus button click.
        tr
          td on
          td object
          td
          td
            p Object with events handlers. For example:
            :code(lang="js")
                  var stepper = app.stepper.create({
                    el: '.stepper',
                    on: {
                      change: function () {
                        console.log('Stepper value changed')
                      }
                    }
                  })

